SUMMARY:Historic Buildings Walking Tour!
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Explorer Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tours\, email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or for signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticket amount when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nToronto has a rich history\, and it's all around us\, but certain buildings do stand out and tell our story. On this walking tour the following buildings are explored and their history revealed. This new tour is for residents and tourists who want to reconnect with their city\, or get to know it from a different vantage point!\n\n* Daniel Brooke Building\n* St. Lawrence Hall\n* St. James Anglican Cathedral\n* St. Michael's Cathedral\n* Mackenzie House\n* Massey Hall\n* Old City Hall\n* Osgoode Hall\n* Campbell House Museum\n* Gooderham Building\n\nand a few other hidden surprises along the way from the Toronto Stock Exchange to the New City Hall and a few others in between!\n\nThis walking tour is for all walking levels. Please dress for the season\, and hope to see you there.\n\nPlease meet in front of the iconic St. Lawrence Hall at the corner of Jarvis and King Street East\, we end the tour at Historic Campbell House!\n\nThis tour has a ticket price of $15.00 per person.\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticket amount when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**
